While researching this topic, I was most surprised by how easily individuals can become victims of cybercrime, especially in cases of UPI and online payment fraud. 
Many scams do not involve complex hacking but instead rely on simple psychological manipulation, such as creating urgency or pretending to be a trusted source. This made me realize that even basic mistakes, like clicking unknown links or approving suspicious requests, can lead to serious consequences.

As a result, one habit I will personally change is being more cautious while handling digital transactions. 
I will ensure that I verify every request and avoid sharing any sensitive information, such as OTPs or UPI PINs, under any circumstances. This awareness will help me use digital platforms more safely and responsibly.
